8. Implementation of risk management policy and risk measurement standards: The Company has established the internal control system, internal audit system, self-evaluation procedure, and various management regulations or operating procedures which serve to be the risk management policy and risk measurement criteria followed by the Company’s units and audit unit when they are carrying out the operations mentioned above.

9. Status of consumers protection or customers’ policy: In order to take care of the omnibus service and protection for customers, the Company will immediately communicate with the customers who file a complaint to verify their needs and facilitate the interactive effect between the Company and customers. The Company will also review and improve the defect at its production and marketing meeting and quality control meeting.

10. Purchase of liability insurance by the Company for directors and independent directors: The Company has continued to purchase liability insurance for its directors and independent directors each year since 2011 until now, and also disclosed it on the M.O.P.S., and reported it to the board meeting on March 19, 2018.

11. Communication between the independent directors, head of internal audit and independent

auditor:

(1). Prepare the “summarization of audit report” and submit the same, together with a copy of the audit report, to each audit committee member for review, on a monthly basis.

(2). Should the audit committee member have any question or instruction upon reviewing the audit report, he/she will call the head of audit for consultation or instruction.

(3). Each audit report shall follow up the improvement of deficiency in internal control and extraordinary circumstances after 3 months, and compile and submit the follow-up report to each audit committee member.
